= SDL_WaitEvent =
Use this function to wait indefinitely for the next available event.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_WaitEvent(SDL_Event* event)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''event'''
|if not NULL, the next event is removed from the queue and stored in that area ''-or-'' ^the [[SDL_Event]] structure to be filled in with the next event from the queue, or NULL^
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 1 on success or 0 if there was an error while waiting for events; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

